org.jlab.coda.emu.support.codaComponent

Enum CODATransition

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<CODATransition>
      • org.jlab.coda.emu.support.codaComponent.CODATransition
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<CODATransition>

    public enum CODATransition
extends java.lang.Enum<CODATransition>
    An enum which contains a list of possible transitions in CODA Emu state machine. Each of these transitions can be enabled or disabled. 
    
                 *****************
                 * State Machine *
                 *****************
 _________________________________________________________________
                 |                 |
    transition   |      STATE      |  transition
 ________________|_________________|______________________________

                               (if reset from ERROR or BOOTED)
                  <- BOOTED <-----------------------------,
                 |                                        |
     configure   |                                        |
                 |               <------------------------|
                 '-> CONFIGURED ->----------------------->|
                  <-                                      ^
                 |                                        |
     download    |                                        |
                 |                                        |
                 '-> DOWNLOADED ->----------------------->|
                  <-            <-,<----------,           ^
                 |                ^           ^           |
                 |                |           |           |
     prestart    |                | end       | end       | reset
                 |                |           |           |
                 '-> PAUSED -----> -----------|---------->|
                  <-                          |           ^
                 |                            |           |
        go       |                            |           |
                 |                            |           |
                 '->  ACTIVE  --------------->'---------->'

 __________________________________________________________________

  NOTE: DOWNLOADED can always do a download,
        CONFIGURED can always do a configure, and
        RESET goes from any state to CONFIGURED (to BOOTED if in ERROR or BOOTED state)
    Author:
    heyes, timmer
